FIELD: SWATH GRID LINE and associated data

DESCRIPTION: UTC time of line of nodes
Absolute (unique) counter for the line of nodes (from format version 12.0 onwards only)
Azimuth angle bearing (range: 0 to 360) of nadir track velocity
Ascending/descending pass indicator

Node number as used in the PGF (ref AD-2]), i.e., (10 to -10) for the left swath in the left-to-right order, (-10 to 10) for the right swath in the left-to-right order, 0 corresponding to the mid swath position in both swaths.
Swath (0=LEFT, 1=RIGHT)
Latitude (-90 to 90 deg)
Longitude (0 to 360 deg)
Height of atmosphere used
Atmospheric loss per unit length of atmosphere
Sigma0 triplet, re-sampled to swath grid, for 3 beams (fore, mid, aft)
Kp for re-sampled sigma0 tripplet. Values between 0 and 1
Incidence angle for re-sampled sigma0 tripplet.
Incidence angle for re-sampled sigma0 tripplet. Values range from -180 to +180, where minus is west and plus is east.
Number of full resolution sigma0 values contributing to the re-sampled sigma0 tripplet.
Flag related to the quality of the Kp estimate (0=NOMINAL, 1=NON-NOMINAL)
Flag related to the usability of the sigma0 tripplet (0=GOOD, 1=USABLE, 2=NOT USABLE)
Flag related to non-nominal amount of input raw data to calculate echo corrections (value between 0 and 1 shows the fraction of original samples affected)
Flag related to non enough amount of input raw data to calculate echo corrections (value between 0 and 1 shows the fraction of original samples affected)
Flag related to lack of accuracy of orbit/atticute knowledge (value between 0 and 1 shows the fraction of original samples affected)
Flag related to solar array reflection contamination (value between 0 and 1 shows the fraction of original samples affected)
Flag related to non-nominal telemetry check results (value between 0 and 1 shows the fraction of original samples affected)
Flag related to the presence of extrapolated reference functions in the generation of averaged value (ref. Ad-2) (value between 0 and 1)
Flag related to non-nominal raw echo correction reference functions (value between 0 and 1 shows the fraction of original samples affected)
Flag related to presence of land in the re-sampled sigma0 tripllet (value between 0 and 1 shows the fraction of original samples affected)

Wet backscatter
